&gt;&gt; Sasha Dowdy: Good
afternoon, everybody.

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:22.320
Welcome to the Library
of Congress.

00:00:22.320 --> 00:00:24.830
[Inaudible] for all.

00:00:24.830 --> 00:00:27.190
Welcome, welcome, to the
historic Coolidge Auditorium,

00:00:27.190 --> 00:00:29.050
the Library of Congress
After Hours.

00:00:29.050 --> 00:00:31.180
It's going to be a
really good panel.

00:00:31.180 --> 00:00:33.970
So to introduce myself,
my name is Sasha Dowdy.

00:00:33.970 --> 00:00:36.920
I work here at the library
as program specialist

00:00:36.920 --> 00:00:38.220
at the Young Readers Center.

00:00:38.220 --> 00:00:41.740
So I do programming for
kids who are under 16,

00:00:41.740 --> 00:00:44.500
but sometimes I do
programming for kids over 16.

00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:46.790
So that's why we're all here.

00:00:46.790 --> 00:00:49.970
We have had a series of
events in conjunction

00:00:49.970 --> 00:00:51.590
with Otakon here at the library.

00:00:51.590 --> 00:00:53.250
So we're really excited
to present

00:00:53.250 --> 00:00:55.310
to you a very, very
special guest.

00:00:55.310 --> 00:00:59.500
And now we're going to have a
panel with two library staff,

00:00:59.500 --> 00:01:02.650
and they're going to speak to
an incredible person that we're

00:01:02.650 --> 00:01:05.920
so excited to have here:
Mister Hirokatsu Kihara.

00:01:05.920 --> 00:01:08.090
He's a writer and
producer formally involved

00:01:08.090 --> 00:01:10.650
with the production
desk at Studio Ghilbi ,

00:01:10.650 --> 00:01:14.360
and he was involved in the
hit anime such as "Laputa:

00:01:14.360 --> 00:01:17.210
Castle in the Sky," and
"My Neighbor Totoro,"

00:01:17.210 --> 00:01:18.630
and "Kiki's Delivery Service."

00:01:18.630 --> 00:01:21.470
Any fans of these
movies in here?

00:01:21.470 --> 00:01:23.920
[ Applause ]

00:01:23.920 --> 00:01:26.520
So now he writes ghost stories,

00:01:26.520 --> 00:01:28.710
and he MCs at monster
conventions.

00:01:28.710 --> 00:01:30.090
So there's a lot going on here.

00:01:30.090 --> 00:01:33.790
His most famous work is "Tales
of Terror: Haunted Apartment."

00:01:33.790 --> 00:01:35.800
So -- And he's been
a crucial contributor

00:01:35.800 --> 00:01:37.900
to many other hits in the genre.

00:01:37.900 --> 00:01:41.320
And he's going to be interviewed
by two library staff members.

00:01:41.320 --> 00:01:42.800
Maureen Cohen Harrington.

00:01:42.800 --> 00:01:44.730
She's a senior counsel
in the library's office

00:01:44.730 --> 00:01:46.030
of the general counsel.

00:01:46.030 --> 00:01:47.530
That's lawyers.

00:01:47.530 --> 00:01:50.560
And she feels fortunate
that her law gig allows her

00:01:50.560 --> 00:01:52.380
to explore and expand interests.

00:01:52.380 --> 00:01:55.390
She has an undergrad degree
in radio, television, film,

00:01:55.390 --> 00:01:57.800
and has been to many comic
and pop culture conventions.

00:01:57.800 --> 00:02:00.440
So when she's not here,
she's at San Diego Comic-Con

00:02:00.440 --> 00:02:02.700
and Awesome Con and on and on.

00:02:02.700 --> 00:02:05.700
She's kind of new to anime so
she is going to learn about it

00:02:05.700 --> 00:02:10.090
as she talks with her coworker
in general counsel's office,

00:02:10.090 --> 00:02:12.570
Anthony Dunn, where
he goes by Ant.

00:02:12.570 --> 00:02:16.810
He is a lover of food,
design, cool socks,

00:02:16.810 --> 00:02:18.290
anime, and all things nerdy.

00:02:18.290 --> 00:02:19.870
So he's one of us.

00:02:19.870 --> 00:02:23.380
They're both fans of pop
culture, and inline skating,

00:02:23.380 --> 00:02:25.470
and they discover
lots of new things.

00:02:25.470 --> 00:02:28.290
And, in the spirit of Library
of Congress being an institution

00:02:28.290 --> 00:02:31.110
of learning, we're all going to
learn something new together.

00:02:31.110 --> 00:02:34.890
So let's welcome Mister
Kihara, Maureen, and Ant.

00:02:34.890 --> 00:02:36.690
Come on out.

00:02:36.690 --> 00:02:51.630
[ Applause ]

