00:08:38.360 --> 00:08:40.510
what would your favorite be?

00:08:40.510 --> 00:08:55.830
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:08:55.830 --> 00:08:57.190
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: This year's
the 30th anniversary

00:08:57.190 --> 00:08:59.510
of 30th anniversary of "Totoro."

00:08:59.510 --> 00:09:02.510
[ Applause ]

00:09:02.510 --> 00:09:05.720
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:09:05.720 --> 00:09:08.110
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: April 16, 1988 was

00:09:08.110 --> 00:09:10.510
when it came out
in the theaters.

00:09:10.510 --> 00:09:15.060
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:09:15.060 --> 00:09:19.670
It's truly an honor to come
here to D.C on that special year

00:09:19.670 --> 00:09:20.970
to talk about "Totoro."

00:09:20.970 --> 00:09:26.300
You know, the place that I
had imagined since childhood.

00:09:26.300 --> 00:09:33.510
I was 28 years old at the time.

00:09:33.510 --> 00:09:38.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:09:38.040 --> 00:09:41.040
[Inaudible] told
