It sounds unbelievable,
but I really wanted to work

00:16:53.310 --> 00:16:56.520
with Miyazaki so I showed
up to work every single day.

00:16:56.520 --> 00:16:58.040
The very first one in office,

00:16:58.040 --> 00:17:00.290
and left after the
very last person.

00:17:00.290 --> 00:17:01.590
&gt;&gt; Maureen Cohen
Harrington: Wow.

00:17:01.590 --> 00:17:03.390
&gt;&gt; Anthony Dunn: Wow.

00:17:03.390 --> 00:17:07.290
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:17:07.290 --> 00:17:08.590
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: So I told
myself, "Hard work.

00:17:08.590 --> 00:17:09.890
Hard work.

00:17:09.890 --> 00:17:11.690
Hard work."

00:17:11.690 --> 00:17:26.900
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:17:26.900 --> 00:17:28.200
[Inaudible] Miyazaki
told [inaudible]

00:17:28.200 --> 00:17:30.480
"Don't let this guy quit."

00:17:30.480 --> 00:17:33.410
And he had to make
this guy keep going.

00:17:34.510 --> 00:17:37.190
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:17:37.190 --> 00:17:41.510
At the time he didn't know why.

00:17:41.510 --> 00:17:45.330
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:17:45.330 --> 00:17:48.620
And then one day he patted me on
the shoulder and turned around,

00:17:48.620 --> 00:17:51.600
and he -- Miyazaki was there.

00:17:51.600 --> 00:17:53.510
&gt;&gt; Hirokatsu Kihara: What?

00:17:53.510 --> 00:17:57.060
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:17:57.060 --> 00:18:00.080
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: And he told
me, "You and I are going

00:18:00.080 --> 00:18:01.820
to make Totoro together."

00:18:01.820 --> 00:18:08.510
And that is how "Totoro"
was made 30 years ago.

00:18:08.510 --> 00:18:16.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:18:16.040 --> 00:18:21.020
After making "Castle in the
Sky," they were producing

00:18:21.020 --> 00:18:25.510
"Grave of the Fireflies."

00:18:25.510 --> 00:18:32.680
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:18:32.680 --> 00:18:35.740
So I don't know if you guys
noticed, but "Totoro" and "Grave

00:18:35.740 --> 00:18:38.200
of the Fireflies" was
shown as a double feature.

00:18:38.200 --> 00:18:43.510
"Grave of the Fireflies"
started production first.

00:18:43.510 --> 00:18:49.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:18:49.040 --> 00:18:51.950
But it was good that when
we started working --

00:18:51.950 --> 00:18:53.250
I started working with Miyazaki,

00:18:53.250 --> 00:18:55.170
but then the studio
told us to leave.

00:18:55.170 --> 00:18:57.510
&gt;&gt; Hirokatsu Kihara: Get out.

00:18:57.510 --> 00:19:03.060
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:19:03.060 --> 00:19:05.750
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: Because they had
to use the studio to produce

00:19:05.750 --> 00:19:07.860
"Grave of the Fireflies"
so they told us to leave,

00:19:07.860 --> 00:19:10.510
and build a new studio.

00:19:10.510 --> 00:19:20.140
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:19:20.140 --> 00:19:21.820
So we're doing a long history

00:19:21.820 --> 00:19:25.100
of Ghibli during this
production stage of "Totoro"

00:19:25.100 --> 00:19:26.660
and "Grave of the Fireflies."

00:19:26.660 --> 00:19:29.510
There were two studios.

00:19:29.510 --> 00:19:32.140
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:19:32.140 --> 00:19:35.590
"Totoro" was created in this --

00:19:35.590 --> 00:19:38.340
the second studio that was
only created for that time.

00:19:38.340 --> 00:19:43.600
And after "Totoro" it
was consolidated back

00:19:43.600 --> 00:19:46.010
in to a single studio again.

00:19:46.010 --> 00:19:47.310
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:19:47.310 --> 00:19:52.170
And that was "Kiki's
Delivery Service."

00:19:53.510 --> 00:19:59.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:19:59.040 --> 00:20:03.420
So if you have a special
fondness for "Totoro,"

00:20:03.420 --> 00:20:07.510
that was born under
special circumstances.

00:20:07.510 --> 00:20:20.160
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:20:20.160 --> 00:20:24.010
So you can imagine how insane
it was to be producing "Totoro"

00:20:24.010 --> 00:20:29.030
and "Grave of the
Fireflies" at the same time.

00:20:29.030 --> 00:20:31.320
&gt;&gt; Maureen Cohen Harrington: Is
there a character that you --

00:20:31.320 --> 00:20:33.350
You are so animated yourself

00:20:33.350 --> 00:20:35.720
that I can see why you
are drawn to animation.

00:20:35.720 --> 00:20:39.120
Is there a character who
you relate with most closely

00:20:39.120 --> 00:20:42.510
or feel the most bonded?

00:20:42.510 --> 00:20:47.580
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:20:47.580 --> 00:20:51.510
Yours or someone else's.

00:20:51.510 --> 00:21:04.190
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:21:04.190 --> 00:21:05.520
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: Yes.

00:21:05.520 --> 00:21:10.010
Always laughing all
the time in the studio.

00:21:10.010 --> 00:21:11.350
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:21:11.350 --> 00:21:15.010
And then became the
model for the cat voice.

00:21:15.010 --> 00:21:17.510
[ Screeching ]

00:21:17.510 --> 00:21:20.510
[ Laughter ]

00:21:20.510 --> 00:21:24.230
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:21:24.230 --> 00:21:26.070
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: Hayao Miyazaki
told me that his happiness is

00:21:26.070 --> 00:21:29.510
to be laughing and running.

00:21:29.510 --> 00:21:38.150
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:21:38.150 --> 00:21:40.380
But saying you're sad when
you're sad, and being upset

00:21:40.380 --> 00:21:42.700
when you're upset doesn't
really change anything.

00:21:42.700 --> 00:21:47.030
Then why don't we just
laugh with everybody?

00:21:47.030 --> 00:21:49.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:21:49.040 --> 00:21:54.510
Being able to laugh at
work will bring you hope.

00:21:54.510 --> 00:22:01.110
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:22:01.110 --> 00:22:02.940
We were rushed in production.

00:22:02.940 --> 00:22:05.370
We were not making
anything on time.

00:22:05.370 --> 00:22:08.000
We had to do all this painting,

00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:12.510
and nothing was being
made on time, but --

00:22:12.510 --> 00:22:17.110
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:22:17.110 --> 00:22:20.200
And then we would
all get together and,

00:22:20.200 --> 00:22:23.510
okay, it's thinking time.

00:22:23.510 --> 00:22:28.940
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:22:28.940 --> 00:22:31.530
They say that when
you're laughing,

00:22:31.530 --> 00:22:34.050
then you can create
better ideas.

00:22:35.510 --> 00:22:40.470
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:22:40.470 --> 00:22:44.110
There's only a 10 day
[inaudible] between completion

00:22:44.110 --> 00:22:48.720
of "Castle in the Sky"
and release to theaters.

00:22:48.720 --> 00:22:51.510
10 days. 10 days.

00:22:51.510 --> 00:22:58.810
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:22:58.810 --> 00:23:00.210
"Totoro" there were only 15 days

00:23:00.210 --> 00:23:03.800
between drawing every
single piece of art

00:23:03.800 --> 00:23:07.510
and release in to theaters.

00:23:07.510 --> 00:23:12.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:23:12.040 --> 00:23:14.820
Other studios kept thinking,

00:23:14.820 --> 00:23:18.510
"You're not going
to make it on time."

00:23:18.510 --> 00:23:22.430
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:23:22.430 --> 00:23:26.510
But Takahata, he's like,
"You do not give up."

00:23:26.510 --> 00:23:30.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:23:30.040 --> 00:23:33.480
The desire to create
something great,

00:23:33.480 --> 00:23:36.970
they refused to cut corners.

00:23:36.970 --> 00:23:41.510
That's why they tried hard.

00:23:41.510 --> 00:23:48.260
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:23:48.260 --> 00:23:50.070
If you're making a sad
face, that's not the kind

00:23:50.070 --> 00:23:52.280
of movie that you want to see.

00:23:52.280 --> 00:23:54.550
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:23:54.550 --> 00:24:01.660
You have to grit your
teeth, and just laugh.

00:24:01.660 --> 00:24:04.530
[Inaudible] making
this for children.

00:24:04.530 --> 00:24:07.510
&gt;&gt; Like in skating where
you look where you're going.

00:24:07.510 --> 00:24:13.220
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:24:13.220 --> 00:24:16.890
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: I tripped on it.

00:24:16.890 --> 00:24:19.190
I had a fall.

00:24:20.510 --> 00:24:32.530
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:24:32.530 --> 00:24:37.410
So there are 75,000 in between
[inaudible] pieces of art

00:24:37.410 --> 00:24:41.510
in "Castle in the
Sky" hand drawn.

00:24:41.510 --> 00:24:46.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:24:46.040 --> 00:24:49.780
That means 75,000 individual
pieces of [inaudible]

00:24:49.780 --> 00:24:53.510
that got painted by hand.

00:24:53.510 --> 00:24:58.070
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:24:58.070 --> 00:25:02.510
And that was -- This was
all completed in 10 months.

00:25:02.510 --> 00:25:06.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:25:06.040 --> 00:25:08.020
And this is incredible work.

00:25:08.020 --> 00:25:09.320
It's all hand drawn.

00:25:09.320 --> 00:25:10.620
Not digital.

00:25:10.620 --> 00:25:17.510
There was no software back then.

00:25:17.510 --> 00:25:26.020
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:25:26.020 --> 00:25:27.320
Unimaginable.

00:25:27.320 --> 00:25:29.550
Clicking, you know,
each person that had

00:25:29.550 --> 00:25:32.510
to be hand photographed.

00:25:32.510 --> 00:25:36.920
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:25:36.920 --> 00:25:40.510
People who give up
can't do animation.

00:25:40.510 --> 00:25:44.190
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:25:44.190 --> 00:25:48.260
So people who love animation
are people who don't give up.

00:25:48.260 --> 00:25:52.180
So that's why he has --
They have his respect.

00:25:52.180 --> 00:25:56.510
That is true for everybody here.

00:25:56.510 --> 00:26:00.240
[ Applause ]

00:26:00.240 --> 00:26:04.980
&gt;&gt; Anthony Dunn: So what was
your favorite movie to work at,

00:26:04.980 --> 00:26:08.510
work on, at Studio Ghibli?

00:26:08.510 --> 00:26:20.360
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:26:20.360 --> 00:26:22.870
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: "Castle
in the Sky" was --

00:26:22.870 --> 00:26:26.510
created the most hardship
for everybody, though.

00:26:26.510 --> 00:26:31.250
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:26:31.250 --> 00:26:32.850
"Kiki's Delivery
Service" was the one

00:26:32.850 --> 00:26:36.570
that had the hardest schedule,
and everybody had to, you know,

00:26:36.570 --> 00:26:39.510
be rushing from the start.

00:26:39.510 --> 00:26:45.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:47.770
"Totoro" looks so fun on screen,

00:26:47.770 --> 00:26:53.510
but in the very beginning
Miyazaki gave me one order.

00:26:53.510 --> 00:27:02.130
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:27:02.130 --> 00:27:03.430
This is a fun movie.

00:27:03.430 --> 00:27:06.160
You have to be having
fun making it.

00:27:06.160 --> 00:27:09.510
That is my only order to you.

00:27:09.510 --> 00:27:16.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:27:16.040 --> 00:27:19.290
So I felt that somebody had
to be, you know, smiling

00:27:19.290 --> 00:27:22.030
and laughing somewhere
in this idea.

00:27:23.510 --> 00:27:27.200
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:27:27.200 --> 00:27:30.630
I mean that's an ideal, but
it's hard to do when you --

00:27:30.630 --> 00:27:34.010
You know, it's a tough schedule.

00:27:34.010 --> 00:27:35.310
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:27:35.310 --> 00:27:40.510
But I think it was
possible just for "Totoro."

00:27:40.510 --> 00:27:46.260
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:27:46.260 --> 00:27:48.580
"Castle in the Sky" was tough
because I had to manage a studio

00:27:48.580 --> 00:27:52.510
at the same time as
working on the production.

00:27:52.510 --> 00:27:58.880
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:27:58.880 --> 00:28:02.640
"Kiki's" was behind schedule
from the very beginning.

00:28:02.640 --> 00:28:05.510
So that's why it was tough.

00:28:05.510 --> 00:28:18.190
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:28:18.190 --> 00:28:21.090
I think it's amazing that
Miyazaki continues to be loved

00:28:21.090 --> 00:28:23.750
around the world after 30 years.

00:28:25.510 --> 00:28:30.250
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:28:30.250 --> 00:28:32.370
Because I never gave up,
and always worked hard,

00:28:32.370 --> 00:28:36.560
the result is that I'm here
today in front of all of you.

00:28:36.560 --> 00:28:40.510
And grateful to every
single one of you.

00:28:40.510 --> 00:28:44.710
[ Applause ]

00:28:44.710 --> 00:28:48.510
&gt;&gt; Anthony Dunn: So what
made you leave Studio Ghibli?

00:28:48.510 --> 00:28:52.140
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:28:52.140 --> 00:28:55.360
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: That
is a tough question.

00:28:56.510 --> 00:29:07.270
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:29:07.270 --> 00:29:11.510
So it was "Kiki's" that
finally became profitable.

00:29:11.510 --> 00:29:16.750
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:29:16.750 --> 00:29:21.510
Financially, "Castle in
the Sky" was not a success.

00:29:21.510 --> 00:29:24.210
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:29:24.210 --> 00:29:28.070
It just wasn't a failure.

00:29:28.070 --> 00:29:30.120
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:29:30.120 --> 00:29:36.510
But Kiki's was a big success.

00:29:36.510 --> 00:29:41.420
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:29:41.420 --> 00:29:47.510
And sold a lot of laser disks
which was unknown at the time.

00:29:47.510 --> 00:29:53.120
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:29:53.120 --> 00:29:55.160
When a studio becomes
financially profitable,

00:29:55.160 --> 00:29:58.510
it attracts a lot of people.

00:29:58.510 --> 00:30:02.420
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:30:02.420 --> 00:30:08.270
And they don't necessarily
love the medium.

00:30:08.270 --> 00:30:11.510
&gt;&gt; Hirokatsu Kihara: It's money.

00:30:11.510 --> 00:30:18.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:30:18.040 --> 00:30:21.020
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: It becomes hard
to work when there's a lot

00:30:21.020 --> 00:30:24.250
of people who don't feel love
for what they're creating.

00:30:25.510 --> 00:30:39.170
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:30:39.170 --> 00:30:41.720
I'd become like a
hindrance to the people

00:30:41.720 --> 00:30:45.510
who were trying to make money.

00:30:45.510 --> 00:30:48.710
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:30:48.710 --> 00:30:51.180
Because I'm thinking about the,
you know -- every single worker.

00:30:51.180 --> 00:30:58.510
I want to be on the side of
the staff and the director.

00:30:58.510 --> 00:31:07.150
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:31:07.150 --> 00:31:09.910
For people on the
business side of things,

00:31:09.910 --> 00:31:14.480
that's not necessarily
a good thing.

00:31:14.480 --> 00:31:17.510
That's why I left.

00:31:17.510 --> 00:31:23.890
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:31:23.890 --> 00:31:25.950
Before that, I had to
manage the schedules

00:31:25.950 --> 00:31:30.510
and audio of 200 people.

00:31:30.510 --> 00:31:34.150
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:31:34.150 --> 00:31:39.310
So I just wanted to take
care of myself from then on.

00:31:39.310 --> 00:31:42.510
And that's how I
became a writer.

00:31:42.510 --> 00:32:09.040
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:32:09.040 --> 00:32:13.350
So then since a lot of animists
use new media, they started

00:32:13.350 --> 00:32:15.470
to call on me for
uncredited help

00:32:15.470 --> 00:32:18.510
with various stages
of production.

00:32:18.510 --> 00:32:27.410
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:32:27.410 --> 00:32:28.710
So [inaudible] first --

00:32:28.710 --> 00:32:31.520
Eventually they went on
to create [inaudible]

00:32:31.520 --> 00:32:35.090
but on the first
animated they worked on,

00:32:35.090 --> 00:32:38.510
I did a lot of work for them.

00:32:38.510 --> 00:32:47.620
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:32:47.620 --> 00:32:50.200
And there was also a
movie called "Gundam F91"

00:32:50.200 --> 00:32:54.870
which I did a lot of work on to
get them to release on schedule.

00:32:54.870 --> 00:32:58.880
I just told them
to not credit me.

00:32:58.880 --> 00:33:01.200
I didn't want it.

00:33:01.200 --> 00:33:09.050
Because I got my, you know,
fame through Miyazaki.

00:33:09.050 --> 00:33:11.080
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:33:11.080 --> 00:33:14.600
Because if I put my name
out there, then there's only

00:33:14.600 --> 00:33:15.900
like three other people

00:33:15.900 --> 00:33:19.010
who don't get their
work appreciated.

00:33:19.010 --> 00:33:20.310
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:33:20.310 --> 00:33:25.510
So I shouldn't take their,
you know, spot [inaudible].

00:33:25.510 --> 00:33:28.080
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:33:28.080 --> 00:33:30.040
So it looks like my work

00:33:30.040 --> 00:33:35.040
in animation just stopped
after I left Ghibli.

00:33:35.040 --> 00:33:37.070
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:33:37.070 --> 00:33:39.200
But there's a lot of people

00:33:39.200 --> 00:33:41.070
in the animation
industry right now who,

00:33:41.070 --> 00:33:44.510
you know, started work with me.

00:33:44.510 --> 00:33:50.080
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:33:50.080 --> 00:33:52.540
So I'm very happy that so many

00:33:52.540 --> 00:33:55.720
of my friends are still
continuing in making anime

00:33:55.720 --> 00:33:58.510
in the industry right now.

00:33:58.510 --> 00:34:07.500
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:34:07.500 --> 00:34:13.300
There's a movie right now called
"In the Corner of this World."

00:34:13.300 --> 00:34:18.970
Mister Katabuchi used to work on
-- On "Kiki's Delivery Service?"

00:34:18.970 --> 00:34:25.510
He was an assistant director.

00:34:25.510 --> 00:34:43.850
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:34:43.850 --> 00:34:48.370
And the super hit "Your Name,"
the art director for that work,

00:34:48.370 --> 00:34:52.040
Mister [inaudible] was one
of the very first people

00:34:52.040 --> 00:34:54.390
who got hired by Ghibli.

00:34:56.510 --> 00:34:59.550
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:34:59.550 --> 00:35:01.110
It was "Code Geass."

00:35:01.110 --> 00:35:02.410
Ever heard of "Code Geass?"

00:35:02.410 --> 00:35:04.010
&gt;&gt; Anthony Dunn: Yeah.

00:35:04.010 --> 00:35:05.810
[ Laughter ]

00:35:05.810 --> 00:35:18.400
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:35:18.400 --> 00:35:20.590
&gt;&gt; Speaker 2: I personally chose
Mister [inaudible] who worked

00:35:20.590 --> 00:35:22.250
on "Code Geass," and he --

00:35:22.250 --> 00:35:26.510
hand picked him to
be working on Ghibli.

00:35:26.510 --> 00:35:32.480
[ Foreign Language Spoken ]

00:35:32.480 --> 00:35:38.360
So all these seeds that were
planted along the way has been

00:35:38.360 --> 00:35:45.510
[inaudible] to find trees,
and he's very proud of that.

00:35:45.510 --> 00:35:50.850
[ Applause ]

